Project
======
Stage-1 (Incorporating Signals)
 - Complete all the todos (1 to 5) in libsig.c
 - Complete todos in server.c to register the signal

Stage-2 (Transfer EM registers from server to client using FIFO)
 - Complete todos (2 to 6) in server.c to set up & write the EM registers to FIFO
 - Complete todos (1 & 2) in client.c to set up the FIFO and read the EM register from FIFO
 - Compile with make. Execute client.exe & server.exe in different shells
 - The server display the library files in the current directory and send out the em registers over FIFO
 - The client.exe should display values of Va, Vb and Vc sent out from the server

Stage-3 (Update the Energy management registers)
+ Complete all the TODOs in update_registers.c & server.c (todos 7 to 12)
+ Complete the TODOs in libsem.c (1 to 5)
+ Execute all the 3 and the output from the client should display the register values periodically

Stage-4 (Calculate max values by using thread)
+ Complete all the TODOs in register_update.c (todos 7 to 11)
+ Compile & execute register_updated.exe, server.exe and client.exe.
+ Observe the values changing for Va max, Vb max & Vc max

Stage-5 (Synchronize the access to registers)
+ Complete all the TODOs in register_update.c (todos 12 to 21)
+ Compile & execute register_updated.exe, server.exe and client.exe.
+ Observe the values changing for Va max, Vb max & Vc max

Stage-6 (Communicate using the socket)
+ Replace FIFO with socket in client.c & server.
